726288f-a.folder: Browvale Drive & Northern Boulevard, Queens, NY
726288f-a.text:
Browvale Drive, east side, south from Northern Boulevard, then turning east. This area is known as Browvale Hills, Little Neck, "where nature did her best," according to the outdoor sign.
P. L. Sperr  April 12, 1927

727520f-a.folder: Northern Boulevard & Browvale Drive, Queens, NY
727520f-a.text:
Northern Boulevard, north side, at Browvale Drive, Little Neck, showing an old home, now a roadside shop of garden accessories.
P. L. Sperr          June 10, 1927

727521f-a.folder: Northern Boulevard & Browvale Drive, Queens, NY
727521f-a.text:
Northern Boulevard at Browvale Drive, Little Neck, viewing eastward. In the foreground, on the north side of the Boulevard, is an old cemetery, referred to by Mr. Sperr as the "Indian graveyard."

June 10, 1927
Views 1,2

P.L. Sperr
